rass.extraDescription:
It is recommended to perform RASS assessment in all patients admitted to hospital, as well as in all patients on mechanical ventilation.
• In patients with RASS of -3 points or less, sedation should be reduced or changed until reaching -2 to 0 points on the RASS scale;
• Patients with RASS of 2 points or more are insufficiently sedated and require determination of the cause of agitation (anxiety disorder, delirium, pain) and deepening of sedation until reaching -2 to 0 points on the RASS scale;
• If possible, excessive deepening of sedation (less than -2 points on the RASS scale) should be avoided unless there are indications for it.
